section.section:
A carrier may adjust the community rate only for:
age;
geography based on the following contiguous areas of the State:
the Baltimore metropolitan area;
the District of Columbia metropolitan area;
Western Maryland; and
Eastern and Southern Maryland; and
health status, as provided in subsection (g) of this section.

A discount offered under subparagraph (i) of this paragraph shall be:
applied to reduce the rate otherwise payable by the small employer;
actuarially justified;
offered uniformly to all small employers; and
approved by the Commissioner.

In accordance with § 2701(a) of the Affordable Care Act, a premium rate may vary only by:
whether the health benefit plan covers an individual or a family;
rating area;
age, except that a rate may not vary by more than 3 to 1 for adults; and
tobacco use, except that a rate may not vary by more than 1.5 to 1.
